      • LoginDecode

        public static void LoginDecode(org.json.JSONObject obj,
                               Profile profile)
        Converts the json file returned after logging in, to an array of Strings which contains profile information such as: Songs by the user At some point I hope to return a list of the objects called song instead. That way, we can access information about each song in the main without having to communicate to the server every time.
        Parameters:
        obj - json file which is returned by the server after login

      • saveSongEncode

        public static org.json.JSONObject saveSongEncode(java.lang.String songName,
                                                 SongAlgo song,
                                                 Profile profile)
        Creates a JSONObject for the given song. Stores the length of the song in "length" as the number of notes. Stores the frequencies, durations, and delays, in a single string "song" as "frequency[1] duration[1] delay[1] frequency[2] duration[2] delay[2] ..." Stores the profile's username and password in "username" and "password", Stores the song name into "name"
        Parameters:
        song - song to be save on the server
        Returns:
